// USING THE MATERIALAPP WIDGET

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main(){

  runApp(
      MaterialApp(
          title:"My Flutter App",
          home:Material(
              color: Colors.deepPurpleAccent,
              child: Center(
                  child: Text(
                    "Hello Flutter",
                    textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,
                    style: TextStyle(fontSize: 40,color: Colors.blue),
                  ),
              ),
          ),
      ),
  );
}

1Ô∏è‚É£ Import Statement
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';


Imports the Material Design library.

Gives access to widgets like MaterialApp, Text, Center, Colors, etc.

This is the most commonly used Flutter package.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Main Function
void main(){


main() is the entry point of every Dart/Flutter app.

Execution of the app starts from here.

3Ô∏è‚É£ runApp()
runApp(


Starts the Flutter application.

Takes a Widget as an argument.

The widget passed here becomes the root widget of the app.

4Ô∏è‚É£ MaterialApp
MaterialApp(
  title:"My Flutter App",


Wraps the entire app with Material Design features.

title is the app‚Äôs name (used by the OS, not visible on screen).

5Ô∏è‚É£ home Property
home: Material(


home defines the first screen of the app.

Material widget provides a material-style surface (needed for colors, effects, etc.).

6Ô∏è‚É£ Background Color
color: Colors.deepPurpleAccent,


Sets the background color of the screen.

deepPurpleAccent is a predefined Material color.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Center Widget
child: Center(


Centers its child widget horizontally and vertically on the screen.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Text Widget
child: Text(
  "Hello Flutter",


Displays the text "Hello Flutter" on the screen.

9Ô∏è‚É£ Text Direction
textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,


Sets text direction as Left To Right.

Required when using Text without a MaterialApp or Directionality widget.

üîü Text Styling
style: TextStyle(
  fontSize: 40,
  color: Colors.blue,
),


fontSize: 40 ‚Üí Large text size

color: Colors.blue ‚Üí Text color is blue

‚úÖ Final Output

üì± The app shows:

A deep purple background

Blue text saying ‚ÄúHello Flutter‚Äù

Text is centered on the screen

üß† Simple Summary

main() ‚Üí starts the app

runApp() ‚Üí loads the UI

MaterialApp ‚Üí app structure

Material ‚Üí background surface

Center ‚Üí aligns content

Text ‚Üí displays message
